[2m[36m💭 - When we call `docker.create({name: ..., image: ...})`, the FakeDockerService creates a container with a new random
  UUID as the ID.[0m
[2m[36m💭 - When we call `docker.start(id)` with the DB ID, the fake service can't find the container because it was stored with a
  different ID.[0m
