[2m[36m💭 2. Store the Docker container ID in the DB and use it for subsequent Docker operations.[0m
[2m[36m💭 [0m
[2m[36m💭 Option 1 is cleaner - generate the ID first and pass it to the Docker container create. But the Docker service interface
  doesn't accept an ID. Option 2 makes more sense: I'll store the Docker container ID returned from `docker.create()` in
  the DB config, then use that ID for all subsequent Docker operations.[0m
